snippet.textDisplay: Both are to blame but the greatest  onus is on the government  and authorities for lack of foresight and  lack of planning. This water crisis  has been staring in the face of many states but there are no policies or long term plans.We lurch from one shortage to another year after year after year . Overconstruction,  reckless use of ground water and blatant pollution of existing  water supplies  on top of erratic rainfall  all contribute to this scary shortfall. There are People on the ground  who are doing wonderful work but the babus in government  departments  are least bothered to learn,  help or support  such work. This is going to have to be a team effort with all involved.

snippet.textDisplay:
Faye I like your debates but...
Discrimination based on caste is there from the start. After jagan's announcement, it's kind of joke that everyone is responding as if they have never heard the names of those casts. Different casts have different percentage of reservations, isn't that a discrimination?
AP's CM wanted to remove the stigma of 'only the high casts should rule people'. I have read somewhere that the state's former CM said "who would want to born as SC?" Isn't that a discrimination?
Maybe Jagan wants to show that anyone other than Reddy and Kamma( who has been rulers of AP till now as they were mentioning) can be rulers. 
The baby step to eradicate caste system is to first uplift them from grounds so that no one can talk rubbish and make the names of the castes only good for filling forms.
Sure this might have both pros and cons but don't suddenly act as if he is the first person to talk about casts.
I don't think it(caste) is all he has seen in the selection tho. They might be capable in their own sect.

It is understandable that in any business profit is indispensable but it is not that one should play with the health of a customer. This is about honey but in many businesses this tendency is found. For example in milk business the same situation is prevailing. Milkmen add urea, add other things and sell in the market. Oxytocin injections to the live stock are very common. Another example is of the watermelon selling. In watermelons, sugar injections are given by sellers and sold in the market. No one bothers. Unfortunately common ordinary people are helpless. Honey, milk, watermelon are just few examples. There may be more such businesses.
It is also necessary to investigate the study of CSE.

snippet.textDisplay:
So now mirror now is also taking the lead as the voice of the people but always careful not to cross the line to question the ruling party?
The mixed mandate shows how the mass have been divided but, at the same time it is not happy with the ruling party.
The mass has always been betrayed by the elect. However, this episode has really opened the eyes of the mass of the entire nation. This will reflect in every election henceforth and the mass will be vigilant and shall not fall anymore for unrealistic promises or have any expectations from anyone.
Now, the mass have got to know their weakness that's capitalised and how the system that can be misused for enslaving the mass of the nation in the garb of democracy.
If the mass never wakes up now, they will never. They should know and realise what power they hold and if need be to start boycotts and non cooperation of anything and everything that is not in the best interests of the majority of the mass but, not by rioting or by taking law into their hands. Be it economical reforms, social reforms, security reforms, you name it, the mass can voice and react with full force to be effective immediately.
Especially, the past few years have seen the fall of the common man's interests and welfare, it has been beyond their wildest dreams or imagination. 
Tanvi never saw you being so bold to question the centre for their self focused power grabbing manoeuvres? I wonder, if these efforts are really representing the mass like Faye D' souza at least that seemed convincing.
Khuchidi or kheer or vada pav or any other is not a worry. A hand has fingers of various size, purpose and each is indispensable but, let's not forget the fact that the punch generated can be very powerful and fatal at times.
In a way this mandate by the mass has got what is best possible to check out on the options ( you remember that big question right  if not ... then Who ? Well we got to try something even if it is a change to khichidi otherwise, everyday daal roti and dhokla will be a suffocation especially, for the mass which is used to a wide variety of menus); to see how each party now stands for serving the best interest of the mass and they also have been able to put up a strong opposition ( that too someone who have claimed to be very clean) to monitor and keep check.
Let us see how really the unity in diversity can bring about the change. 
By the way onion prices has shown the farmer a means to really pull the plug and get things to favour their side indeed a valuable lesson hope the farmers get to notice it and be smart. If oil prices can be regulated by production control why not control food production to get things favourable. No point begging, dumping etc cut down production then see how things can be justified at least they won't be bankrupt or have to commit suicide.
God bless!

snippet.textDisplay: Many are not aware that they are violating any traffic rules. Many, who are aware of traffic rules, observe that others are not following the rules so they too join in. If ten cars are parked in a no parking area, some others will also go park their vehicles. Many are getting  hauled up for parking vehicles where there are no 'No Parking' signs anywhere. When such things happen, you cannot argue with the police. When police catch you for some offence you have not committed, still, you cannot argue but just pay the fine. And, why keep all the original papers with you or in the vehicle when they can be stolen or lost may be along with the vehicle too? Why not allow photocopies of the papers that can be verified using the registration numbers?

snippet.textDisplay:
It is a kingfisher story repeating itself. But while the USA in 2008 financial crisis did not come to save Lehmann Brothers, it saved all the others that needed money like Morgan Stanley, Citibank, Goldman Sachs etc. All this mess is happening because the banks are controlled by govt. No private bank would have extended 8000 crores without assets. New promotors will not come on board to take the loan of 8000 crores on the books. So, a big write-off is faced by banks. Govt holding will be very less (perhaps only on 1500 crores of new money banks want to inject) and Naresh Goyal equity would have to be reduced to zero, the new promoter will get the airline very cheaply.
The biggest problem has been the expensive airline fuel sold in India. India needed to find a cheaper way to supply airlines with cheaper fuel. In Jan 2019, airline fuel became cheaper than normal petrol used by cars but it has not been always the case. It is an established fact that Indian currency will keep falling like in the past until foreseeable future. So, all the airlines need to keep hedging the currency(Indian rupee) too.

snippet.textDisplay:
First of all, the logic of playing National Anthem in Movie Theaters is beyond my comprehension. I really don't understand the mindset of our courts in passing such a decision.

But as an Indian, if my countries national anthem is played irrespective at any place, it is a matter of pride for me to stand up for it, cinema hall not withstanding.

A Female journalist named Jyoti Yadav from The Print stated that one of the women who is her friend did not stand because she had her periods and was facing discomfort. Dear women, having period is not an excuse to not respect your countries National Anthem. On one side you want to normalize period taboo in the society in general so people understand that it is not a disease but just a part of a woman's menstrual cycle and that it is a sign that the body is working normally. On the other hand you are again playing the gender card and using that as an excuse. If she was in such a distraught state how come she traveled all the way from her home to the movie theater to watch a movie in the first place.

Although calling such people as anti national was farfetched and not the need of the hour by people who were opposing them. What these bunch of girls also did when they did not stand for national anthem was equivalent to disrespecting their own nation and if needed a legal course of action would have been the right thing to do.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey you guys and dolls who have just crossed eighteen
A maiden chance you have to pick and choose
Your next five year elected king or queen
This chance you have got please do not refuse

In the elections of twenty hundred and nineteen
The choice is yours and you should choose wisely
Choose carefully the one who is morally clean
When you cast your vote, do not elect blindly

We need public-spirited persons to rule our country
Persons whose probity and sagacity are well known
Persons who are chivalrous and who are known for their gallantry
And whose names are spoken well throughout the town.

If for your vote you are offered gratis money or booze
Corruption during elections is the bane of our society
I hope that these inducements you will vehemently refuse
Let us have elections that are clean, not dirty.

JAYASHEKAR GANAPATHY
